    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <section id="page-overview" class="page-content prose max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-indigo-600">üè† House Wiring: Build + Wire + Present</h1>
      <p class="text-xl">
        You will design and build a model ‚Äúhouse‚Äù that includes a power source, multiple switch-controlled branches, and lights.
        Larger groups must build a more complex circuit and include a non-light device.
      </p>

      <div class="bg-indigo-50 p-6 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-indigo-500 not-prose my-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-indigo-800">Quick Links</h3>
        <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>üëâ <strong>Start here:</strong> Read the <span class="font-bold">Tier Requirements</span>.</li>
          <li>üëâ <strong>Don‚Äôt get burned:</strong> Use <span class="font-bold">Definitions</span> (what counts as a branch).</li>
          <li>üëâ <strong>Max points:</strong> Follow the <span class="font-bold">Build Checklist</span>.</li>
          <li>üëâ <strong>Know your grade:</strong> Check the <span class="font-bold">150-point rubric</span>.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2>Timeline</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li><strong>Bring it into school:</strong> <span class="text-indigo-700 font-bold">April 7, 2026</span></li>
        <li><strong>Take it home:</strong> <span class="text-indigo-700 font-bold">April 10, 2026</span></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Project Expectations (Big Ideas)</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li>Neat build, stable structure, and <strong>hidden wiring</strong> when possible.</li>
        <li>Each switch should clearly control its intended load(s).</li>
        <li>Planning matters: roles, communication plan, materials list, and timeline.</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm my-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800">Individual accountability</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 mt-2">
          If a student does not contribute, the teacher may apply an individual grade reduction of up to <strong>50%</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2">Teacher override only (no peer voting).</p>
      </div>
    </section>

