    <!-- APPROVED + DEFINITIONS -->
    <section id="page-approved" class="page-content hidden prose max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-indigo-600">Approved Devices + Definitions</h1>

      <h2>Definition: Branch</h2>
      <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5 shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-slate-700">
          <span class="font-bold">Branch</span> = a separate <span class="font-bold">switch-controlled</span> path powering at least one load.
        </p>
        <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2">
          Example: two bulbs on the same switch still count as <strong>one</strong> branch.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-8">Approved Non-Light Device Options (for tiers that require it)</h2>
      <p>Choose <strong>one</strong> from the list below (unless your teacher approves something else).</p>

      <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 my-4">
        <div class="bg-indigo-50 border-l-4 border-indigo-500 rounded-r-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-indigo-800">Approved</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 text-slate-700">
            <li>Small DC fan</li>
            <li>Piezo buzzer</li>
            <li>Small DC motor</li>
            <li>Doorbell-style push button + buzzer</li>
            <li>Low-voltage outlet powering a low-voltage device (teacher must verify safety)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-rose-50 border-l-4 border-rose-500 rounded-r-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-rose-800">Not Allowed</h3>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 text-slate-700">
            <li>Household AC mains voltage</li>
            <li>Heating elements</li>
            <li>Anything unsafe, sparking, or overheating</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="mt-8">Power Source</h2>
      <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-5 shadow-sm">
        <p class="text-slate-700">
          Your build uses <strong>1 power source</strong>. If your circuit is inconsistent, check connection quality, polarity, and switch wiring.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PLANNING GUIDE -->
    <section id="page-planning" class="page-content hidden prose max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-indigo-600">Planning Form Guide</h1>
      <p>
        Your planning form is part of your grade. Use this page as a guide to answer each prompt thoroughly.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm my-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800">What to include (minimum)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc pl-5">
          <li><strong>Group roles:</strong> who builds structure, who wires, who tests/troubleshoots, who finishes aesthetics.</li>
          <li><strong>Communication plan:</strong> how you‚Äôll coordinate outside class.</li>
          <li><strong>Work location:</strong> where you‚Äôll meet and build.</li>
          <li><strong>Materials list:</strong> structure + fasteners + decorations + wiring materials (and how you‚Äôll get them).</li>
          <li><strong>Timeline:</strong> specific target dates for each phase (base ‚Üí structure ‚Üí wiring ‚Üí troubleshooting ‚Üí aesthetics).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2>Add-ons (help your grade)</h2>
      <p>These are not required, but they can raise your Planning/Documentation score:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6">
        <li><strong>Wiring diagram</strong> (simple schematic)</li>
        <li><strong>Labeled map</strong> (layout labeling switches ‚Üí loads)</li>
        <li><strong>Short reflection</strong> (what worked, what failed, what you‚Äôd change)</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="not-prose bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800">Photo requirement</h3>
        <p class="text-slate-700 mt-2">
          Draw your planned project and take a photo of it (or your digital sketch) so it‚Äôs clearly visible.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CHECKLIST -->
    <section id="page-checklist" class="page-content hidden prose max-w-none">
      <h1 class="text-indigo-600">Build Checklist</h1>

      <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm my-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800">Before you start wiring</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Confirm your tier requirements (branches, lights, device).</li>
          <li>Layout plan: where each switch and light will go.</li>
          <li>Decide how wires will be hidden (channels, underside routing, interior walls).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm my-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800">During wiring</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Test each branch as you build it (don‚Äôt wire everything and hope).</li>
          <li>Keep connections tight and secure (loose connections cause flicker/failure).</li>
          <li>Label branches (tiny tags) during build so troubleshooting is faster.</li>
          <li>Bundle and route wires neatly; hide where possible.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose bg-white border border-slate-200 rounded-lg p-6 shadow-sm my-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800">Final checks (grade savers)</h3>
        <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-slate-700 list-disc pl-5">
          <li>Every switch clearly controls the intended load(s).</li>
          <li>No accidental cross-control (switch A turning on branch B).</li>
          <li>Structure holds up to transport.</li>
          <li>Aesthetics finished (not ‚Äúbare wood + dangling wires‚Äù).</li>
          <li>Bring it in on time.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- RUBRIC -->
