      <h2>Detailed Rubric Table</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose">
        <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-slate-300 border border-slate-300 bg-white">
          <thead class="bg-slate-100">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 border-r w-64">Category</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-center text-sm font-bold text-slate-700 border-r w-24">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left text-sm font-bold text-slate-700">Exceeds / Meets / Developing / Beginning</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-200">

            <!-- A -->
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium border-r">A. Meets Specs & Expected Complexity</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold border-r">30</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold text-slate-900">Exceeds (30):</span> Meets your tier targets (branches, lights, device if required) and the design shows intentional planning beyond the minimum.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold text-slate-900">Meets (26):</span> Hits tier targets with minor omissions (e.g., one minor spec issue) but overall matches the plan.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold text-slate-900">Developing (20):</span> Misses multiple tier targets OR includes a device/load count mismatch.</div>
                <div><span class="font-bold text-slate-900">Beginning (10):</span> Major spec misses; incomplete build relative to tier.</div>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <!-- B -->
            <tr class="bg-indigo-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium border-r">B. Circuit Functionality & Control</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-indigo-700 border-r">35</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Exceeds (35):</span> All branches work reliably; switches control intended loads cleanly; no intermittent connections; device works (if required).</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Meets (30):</span> Mostly reliable; one minor glitch or small troubleshooting needed, but overall functions.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Developing (22):</span> Multiple failures or confusion in control (cross-control, flicker, loose connections) but some parts work.</div>
                <div><span class="font-bold">Beginning (12):</span> Largely nonfunctional; cannot demonstrate working control system.</div>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <!-- C -->
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium border-r">C. Wiring Quality (Neat + Hidden)</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold border-r">25</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Exceeds (25):</span> Wiring is routed cleanly, secured, organized; wire is hidden almost everywhere; connections are consistent and safe.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Meets (21):</span> Mostly neat; wire hidden in many places; a few visible runs or mild clutter; connections stable.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Developing (16):</span> Messy routing; many exposed wires; weak organization; increases troubleshooting risk.</div>
                <div><span class="font-bold">Beginning (8):</span> Tangled/exposed wiring throughout; poor connections; difficult to follow or unsafe handling.</div>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <!-- D -->
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium border-r">D. Build Quality & Durability</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold border-r">20</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Exceeds (20):</span> Solid structure; straight edges; holds up to transport; layout makes sense (rooms/areas clearly defined).</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Meets (17):</span> Stable; minor crooked/loose elements; transport mostly safe.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Developing (12):</span> Unstable areas; weak attachments; parts shift during demo/transport.</div>
                <div><span class="font-bold">Beginning (6):</span> Fragile; collapsing/unsafe for transport; major rebuild needed.</div>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <!-- E -->
            <tr class="bg-slate-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium border-r">E. Aesthetics / Realism</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold border-r">20</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Exceeds (20):</span> Finished ‚Äúhouse‚Äù look: thoughtful design, clean surfaces, details, and intentional presentation.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Meets (17):</span> Looks like a house; some finishing present; a few rough areas.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Developing (12):</span> Minimal finishing; looks incomplete or rushed.</div>
                <div><span class="font-bold">Beginning (6):</span> Little/no aesthetic effort; exposed build elements dominate.</div>
                <div class="text-xs text-slate-500 mt-2">
                  Tier expectation increases with group size (largest groups held to the highest finish standard).
                </div>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <!-- F -->
            <tr>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium border-r">F. Planning + Documentation</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold border-r">15</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Exceeds (15):</span> Complete plan: roles, communication, work location, detailed materials list + acquisition plan, timeline with target dates; includes photo/sketch. Add-ons included (diagram/map/reflection).</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Meets (13):</span> Planning form completed with good detail; photo/sketch included; at least one add-on.</div>
                <div class="mb-2"><span class="font-bold">Developing (9):</span> Form incomplete or vague; missing key details (materials/timeline/roles) or missing sketch/photo.</div>
                <div><span class="font-bold">Beginning (4):</span> Minimal planning evidence.</div>
              </td>
            </tr>

            <!-- G -->
            <tr class="bg-indigo-50">
              <td class="px-4 py-3 font-medium border-r">G. Demo + Explanation</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-center font-bold text-indigo-700 border-r">5</td>
              <td class="px-4 py-3 text-sm text-slate-700">
